.TH "spmi_ext_register_readl" 9 "spmi_ext_register_readl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spmi_ext_register_readl \- extended register read long
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spmi_ext_register_readl
.BI "(struct spmi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "u16 addr "  ","
.BI "u8 *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
SPMI device.
.IP "addr" 12
slave register address (16-bit address).
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to be populated with data from the Slave.
.IP "len" 12
the request number of bytes to read (up to 8 bytes).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads up to 8 bytes of data from the extended register space on a
Slave device using 16-bit address.
